Padwa says "Yes there was a terrible war.  It started with arguments and
violence amongst the younger garou.  The shamans from both the 'were-wolf'
and the 'were-panther' tribes saw the wrongness of the war and tried to
stop it.  We tried to teach them the balance and harmony with nature that
Gaia has tried to teach us.  The young garou would not listen.  They 
assumed balance and harmony meant harmony of not living with the opposite
tribe.  The violence started with simply stealing the other tribes hunts.
Then it moved to actual killing of a member of the opposite tribe.  These
strikes and random killings went on for years.  The leaders of the tribes
tried to stop it, but soon found themselves attacking each other as well.
Finally bloodshed occurred in the guild halls themselves.  This escalation
continued until the 'were-panther' tribe realized that this would only end
in extinction.  They decided to leave.  I stayed behind in hopes of teaching
the garou this sad tale and hopefully one day we will learn from our mistakes
and reunite the garou once again.
